M- Medium bodied, refreshing, slightly juicy, nice carbonation, very easy to drink.
O- This was a very nice pale ale, one of my favorites. The only one I would say is maybe a little bit better that I've had is Row 2/Hill 56. Has a very nice hop taste for a pale ale and is very well balanced between the citrus hops and caramel/pale malts. I will definitely be drinking this one again. Definitely recommend trying it if you get the chance. 1,165 charactersjaasen64, Aug 17, 2012
